# QuadSpawnSystem  (sbx)

## Purpose
Owns the creation of world-space demo quads. Returns early until SandboxConfigSingletonComponent
is available. On the first ready frame it seeds the persistent demo quads (a flat colour quad, a
textured quad, an orbiting colour-cycling quad, and two overlapping layered quads) and creates
SpawnerSingletonComponent, whose presence is the "already seeded" guard. On every later frame,
when the spacebar was pressed this frame (InputStateSingletonComponent), it spawns one temporary
spinning quad carrying a LifetimeComponent and increments the spawn count.

## Input Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| SandboxConfigSingletonComponent | read | Texture ids for seeded quads; guard (returns early if absent) |
| InputStateSingletonComponent | read | A fresh spacebar press triggers a spawn |
| SpawnerSingletonComponent | write | Guard + spawn count |

## Output Components
| Component | Access | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| SpawnerSingletonComponent | write / add (deferred) | Created once; spawn count incremented per spawn |
| QuadComponent | add (deferred) | Seeded persistent quads and spawned temporary quads |
| SpinComponent | add (deferred) | Animation parameters for every created quad |
| LifetimeComponent | add (deferred) | Only on spawned (temporary) quads |
